com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.Datase.name: customers
com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.Datase.description: This table has basic information about a customer, as well as some derived facts based on a customer's orders

fields.description: This is a unique identifier for a customer
Date (UTC) of a customer's first order
Date (UTC) of a customer's most recent order
Count of the number of orders a customer has placed

com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.ViewPr.viewLogic:
with customers as (

    select * from {{ ref('stg_customers') }}

),

orders as (

    select * from {{ ref('stg_orders') }}

),

payments as (

    select * from {{ ref('stg_payments') }}

),

customer_orders as (

        select
        customer_id,

        min(order_date) as first_order,
        max(order_date) as most_recent_order,
        count(order_id) as number_of_orders
    from orders

    group by customer_id

),

customer_payments as (

    select
        orders.customer_id,
        sum(amount) as total_amount

    from payments

    left join orders on
         payments.order_id = orders.order_id

    group by orders.customer_id

),

final as (

    select
        customers.customer_id,
        customers.first_name,
        customers.last_name,
        customer_orders.first_order,
        customer_orders.most_recent_order,
        customer_orders.number_of_orders,
        customer_payments.total_amount as customer_lifetime_value

    from customers

    left join customer_orders
        on customers.customer_id = customer_orders.customer_id

    left join customer_payments
        on  customers.customer_id = customer_payments.customer_id

)

select * from final

com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.Datase.name: orders
com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.Datase.description: This table has basic information about orders, as well as some derived facts based on payments

fields.description: This is a unique identifier for an order
Foreign key to the customers table
Date (UTC) that the order was placed

Orders can be one of the following statuses:

| status         | description                                                                                                            |
|----------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| placed         | The order has been placed but has not yet left the warehouse                                                           |
| shipped        | The order has ben shipped to the customer and is currently in transit                                                  |
| completed      | The order has been received by the customer                                                                            |
| return_pending | The customer has indicated that they would like to return the order, but it has not yet been received at the warehouse |
| returned       | The order has been returned by the customer and received at the warehouse                                              |
Amount of the order (AUD) paid for by credit card
Amount of the order (AUD) paid for by coupon
Amount of the order (AUD) paid for by bank transfer
Amount of the order (AUD) paid for by gift card

com.linkedin.pegasus2avro.dataset.ViewPr.formattedViewLogic:
with orders as (

    select * from `calm-pagoda-323403`.`jaffle_shop`.`stg_orders`

),

payments as (

    select * from `calm-pagoda-323403`.`jaffle_shop`.`stg_payments`

),

order_payments as (

    select
        order_id,

        sum(case when payment_method = 'credit_card' then amount else 0 end) as credit_card_amount,
        sum(case when payment_method = 'coupon' then amount else 0 end) as coupon_amount,
        sum(case when payment_method = 'bank_transfer' then amount else 0 end) as bank_transfer_amount,
        sum(case when payment_method = 'gift_card' then amount else 0 end) as gift_card_amount,
        sum(amount) as total_amount

    from payments

    group by order_id

),

final as (

    select
        orders.order_id,
        orders.customer_id,
        orders.order_date,
        orders.status,

        order_payments.credit_card_amount,

        order_payments.coupon_amount,

        order_payments.bank_transfer_amount,

        order_payments.gift_card_amount,

        order_payments.total_amount as amount

    from orders


    left join order_payments
        on orders.order_id = order_payments.order_id

)

select * from final

datasetAssertion.logic:
-- Refunds have a negative amount, so the total amount should always be >= 0.
-- Therefore return records where this isn't true to make the test fail
select
    order_id,
    sum(amount) as total_amount
from `calm-pagoda-323403`.`jaffle_shop`.`orders`
group by 1
having not(total_amount >= 0)
